      "question": "In a town planning project, a triangular park $\\triangle ABC$ is designed such that $\\angle B = 90^\\circ$. A straight path $BD$ is constructed perpendicular to the side $AC$ to provide drainage. It is given that the length of segment $AD = 4 \\text{ cm}$ and $CD = 9 \\text{ cm}$. The site engineer needs to calculate the dimensions of the park to ensure proper fencing and area allocation.",
      "type": "case_study",
      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "What is the length of the drainage path $BD$?",
          "answer": "(C)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $4 \\text{ cm}$",
            "(B) $5 \\text{ cm}$",
            "(C) $6 \\text{ cm}$",
            "(D) $13 \\text{ cm}$"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "In $\\triangle ABC$, $\\angle B = 90^\\circ$ and $BD \\perp AC$.",
              "By the property of right triangles, $BD^2 = AD \\times CD$.",
              "$BD^2 = 4 \\times 9 = 36$.",
              "$BD = 6 \\text{ cm}$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$BD^2 = AD \\cdot CD \\Rightarrow BD^2 = 4 \\cdot 9 = 36 \\Rightarrow BD = 6$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "Find the length of side $AB$.",
          "answer": "(A)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $\\sqrt{52} \\text{ cm}$",
            "(B) $10 \\text{ cm}$",
            "(C) $\\sqrt{48} \\text{ cm}$",
            "(D) $8 \\text{ cm}$"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "In $\\triangle ABD$, by Pythagoras theorem, $AB^2 = AD^2 + BD^2$.",
              "$AB^2 = 4^2 + 6^2 = 16 + 36 = 52$.",
              "$AB = \\sqrt{52} \\text{ cm}$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$AB^2 = AD^2 + BD^2 \\Rightarrow AB^2 = 4^2 + 6^2 = 52 \\Rightarrow AB = \\sqrt{52}$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the ratio of the area of $\\triangle ABD$ to the area of $\\triangle BCD$.",
          "answer": "$4:9$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Both triangles share the same altitude $BD$ relative to bases $AD$ and $CD$ if we view them as triangles on line $AC$.",
              "Alternatively, $\\triangle ABD \\sim \\triangle ACB$ and $\\triangle BCD \\sim \\triangle ACB$.",
              "The ratio of areas is proportional to the square of their corresponding sides.",
              "Area ratio = $(AD/BD)^2 = (4/6)^2 = 16/36 = 4/9$ (or via base ratio $AD/CD = 4/9$ since they share altitude $BD$)."
            ],
            "derivation": "\\frac{\\text{Area}(\\triangle ABD)}{\\text{Area}(\\triangle BCD)} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{2} \\cdot AD \\cdot BD}{\\frac{1}{2} \\cdot CD \\cdot BD} = \\frac{AD}{CD} = \\frac{4}{9}"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iv",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Determine the length of the side $BC$.",
          "answer": "$\\sqrt{117} \\text{ cm}$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "In $\\triangle BCD$, $\\angle BDC = 90^\\circ$.",
              "By Pythagoras theorem, $BC^2 = BD^2 + CD^2$.",
              "$BC^2 = 6^2 + 9^2 = 36 + 81 = 117$.",
              "$BC = \\sqrt{117} \\text{ cm}$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$BC^2 = BD^2 + CD^2 \\Rightarrow BC^2 = 6^2 + 9^2 = 117 \\Rightarrow BC = \\sqrt{117}$"
          }
        }
      ],
